window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A collection of 12 “lush and deliciously sinister fairy tales” (Kelly Link) by the</b> <b><i>New York Times </i></b><b>best-selling author of </b><b><i>The Hazel Wood </i></b><b>and </b><b><i>The Night Country</i></b><b>!</b></p> <p>Before <i>The Hazel Wood</i>, there was Althea Proserpine's <i>Tales from the Hinterland</i>....</p> <p>Journey into the Hinterland, a brutal and beautiful world where a young woman spends a night with Death, brides are wed to a mysterious house in the trees, and an enchantress is killed twice - and still lives.</p> <p>Perfect for new listeners and dedicated fans alike.</p> <p><b>A Macmillan Audio production from Flatiron Books</b></p> <p>\"Albert’s rich and tightly focused collection forms the core of the mythology created in her novels, and her fans will be thrilled at this further glimpse into that world.\" (<i>Booklist</i>, starred review)</p>"; 
